            <p class="aashima-verdict">
              <strong>Why I loved it</strong>
              Dostoyevsky writes psychological collapse better than anyone. Raskolnikov's guilt doesn't arrive dramatically, it seeps. By the end I was exhausted in the way only truly great books manage. This one got under my skin and stayed there.
